{{italic}}'''''Dictionary of Occult, Hermetic and Alchemical Sigils''''', written by [[:fr:Fred Gettings|Fred Gettings]] in 1981, is a massive reference, guide & source book, which examines variations in, developments of, & meanings of [[sigil (magic)|sigil]]s & symbols, used by [[occultists]], [[alchemists]], [[astrologers]], [[hermeticists]], [[magician (paranormal)|magician]]s & others, over the past millennium.<ref name="Pagel">{{cite journal|last1=Pagel|first1=Walter|title=Dictionary of occult, hermetic and alchemical sigils|journal=Medical History|date=1 January 1982|volume=26|issue=1|pages=106–107|pmc=1139128|issn=0025-7273}}</ref><ref name="Fisher">{{cite journal|last1=Fisher|first1=Nicholas|title=Journals and Dictionaries Fred Gettings, Dictionary of occult, hermetic and alchemical sigils. London: Routledge & Kegan Paul, 1981. Pp. 410. £15.95.|journal=The British Journal for the History of Science|date=1983|volume=16|issue=03|pages=317–318|doi=10.1017/S0007087400020197}}</ref><ref name="Multhauf">{{cite journal|last1=Multhauf|first1=Robert P.|title=Fred Gettings, Dictionary of Occult, Hermetic and Alchemical Sigils. London and Boston: Routledge & Kegan Paul, 1981. Pp. 410. $40.|journal=Speculum|date=11 June 2012|volume=58|issue=01|pages=261–262|doi=10.1017/S0038713400157203}}</ref> Contains several thousand sigils from the hermetic, astrological and alchemical tradition. These are classified alphabetically. Gettings also included a useful graphic index which links their graphic form with a related verbal meaning and this would make it much easier to use these sigils meaningfully in [[Ceremonial magic|ceremonies]], etc.
